      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d6946ab1_02926314",
        "filename": "resultdb/cmd/backend/bigquery_export.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 121,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-15T19:19:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i don\u0027t expect this to happen in practice. presumably, nobody would want to exonerate a test variant that does not have unexpected results. however, if someone does, then the same test variant would have expected results marked non-exonerated, and unexpected results marked-exonerated. I think this inconsistent is confusing. Note that exoneration is done at test variant level, not test result level (exoneration does not specify result id)",
      "parentUuid": "2bfc4abb_eb3d3c3d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 119,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 121,
        "endChar": 2
